Fix HUD not rendering: build UI before requiring BuildingConfig

My previous HUD rewrite put require(BuildingConfig) at the very top, before the
ScreenGui was created. On a cold client that require could stall/fail, killing the
whole script so the HUD (balance bar + nav) never appeared at all.

Now the HUD is built first; BuildingConfig is loaded afterward, safely (timeouts +
pcall), and the income readout simply waits for it. Balance/gems/nav no longer
depend on that require, so the HUD always renders.

